       "  'DESCRIPTION': \"Traditions and customs are repeatedly cited as central to Mexican identity. 'Costumbres y tradiciones' are among the top associations with 'México' (13.50%, p1_1a_1|IDE), and both as an advantage of being Indigenous: 12.93% (p13|IND) and 20.27% (p13a_1|IND) mention traditions as the main advantage. This highlights a collective sense that cultural heritage, traditions, and customs are highly valued and important in the conception of what it means to be Mexican.\"},\n",
